  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They kept also the feast of tabernacles, as it is written,.... According to the rules prescribed for the observation of it in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 23:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " this began on the fifteenth day of the seventh month: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and offered the daily burnt offerings by number, according to the custom, as the duty of every day required; for on all the eight days of the feast there was a certain number of sacrifices fixed for every day; and exactly according to the law concerning them did they offer them at this time; see Numbers 29:12. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and offered the daily burnt offerings by number, according to the custom, as the duty of every day required; for on all the eight days of the feast there was a certain number of sacrifices fixed for every day; and exactly according to the law concerning them did they offer them at this time; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 29:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
